\f1\fs32 Pressure is directly proportional to force and inversely proportional to the area over which the force is applied. Increasing the force applied to a surface or decreasing the area increases the pressure. \
Mathematically, pressure is expressed as:  <me>Pressure = \\frac\{Force\}\{Area\}</me>
